li.p:
If we chop R into n pieces, each piece has length \frac{b-a}{\vphantom{\frac12}n}. Then our ith cut is at position a+i\left(\frac{b-a}{n}\right), so our ith piece runs from a+(i-1)\left(\frac{b-a}{n}\right) to a+i\left(\frac{b-a}{n}\right). The approximation of the mass of this piece comes from the density at its midpoint,


m_i\amp=\frac{\left[a+(i-1)\left(\frac{b-a}{n}\right)\right]+\left[a+i\left(\frac{b-a}{n}\right)\right]}{2} 

\amp= a+(i-\tfrac12)\left(\frac{b-a}{n}\right)

